The paper discusses the use of F1000, a post-publication peer review service, for research evaluation in the biomedical literature. While the paper does not directly relate to computer science, it does involve the analysis of large datasets and the comparison of different metrics for research impact. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries) which deals with the organization, retrieval, and distribution of digital information. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval) which deals with the search and retrieval of information from large datasets, cs.CY (Computers and Society) which deals with the social and ethical implications of computing, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) which deals with the protection of information, and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) which deals with the analysis of social networks and their impact on information dissemination.
